# 🛡️ ISO 27001 ISMS – Statement of Applicability

**Organisation:** FirstBank Nigeria Plc (Simulated)
**Standard:** ISO/IEC 27001:2013
**Date:** January 2022
**Document Ref:** FBNPLC-ISMS-SOA-001 | Version 2.0

---

## 📌 Overview

This project documents the Information Security Management System (ISMS) for a simulated Nigerian bank, including a full **Statement of Applicability (SoA)** covering all 114 controls across 14 domains from ISO/IEC 27001:2013 Annex A. Each control is assessed for applicability, implementation status, and justification.

---

## 📋 What's Covered

- ISMS scope definition and boundary setting
- Organisational exclusions with justification
- Full Annex A SoA table (114 controls)
- Implementation status per control (Implemented / Partial / Not Applicable)
- ISMS objectives and KPIs for 2022
- Document version control history

---

## 🔍 Key Controls Assessed

| Domain | Example Controls |
|--------|-----------------|
| A.6 – Organisation of IS | Roles & responsibilities, segregation of duties |
| A.9 – Access Control | RBAC, MFA, privileged access management |
| A.12 – Operations Security | Malware controls, patch management, logging |
| A.16 – Incident Management | CSIRT, incident response procedures |
| A.17 – Business Continuity | BCP/DRP, DR testing |

